                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>On March 30, 1954, President Eisenhower submitted to Congress a special message
                    containing recommendations concerning United States economic foreign policy,
                    based largely on the Randall Commission’s report. For text of the President’s
                    message, see <hi rend="italic">Public Papers of the Presidents of the United
                        States: Dwight D. Eisenhower, 1954,</hi> pages 352–364; Department of State
                        <hi rend="italic">Bulletin,</hi> April 19, 1954, pages 602–607; or <hi
                        rend="italic">House Document No. 360,</hi> 83d Cong., 2d sess.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
